<span id="freeTextContainer4627592134984789554">I have been fascinated by the story of the prison uprising since I was little and saw Al Pacino chanting “Attica!” in Dog Day Afternoon. Despite being a famous event, it has taken over forty years for some of the documents on Attica to be unsealed. Thompson has collected all that information and written a definitive account of the bloody uprising, from the perspectives of both the prisoners and the law enforcement. It is a horrifying, fascinating read on the historical mistreatment of inmates, a</span>
  <span id="freeText4627592134984789554" style="display:none">I have been fascinated by the story of the prison uprising since I was little and saw Al Pacino chanting “Attica!” in Dog Day Afternoon. Despite being a famous event, it has taken over forty years for some of the documents on Attica to be unsealed. Thompson has collected all that information and written a definitive account of the bloody uprising, from the perspectives of both the prisoners and the law enforcement. It is a horrifying, fascinating read on the historical mistreatment of inmates, and how some victims are still searching for justice.<br /><br /><br />Tune in to our weekly podcast dedicated to all things new books, All The Books: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://bookriot.com/listen/shows/allthebooks/">http://bookriot.com/listen/shows/allt...</a><br /></span>
